AB  - This paper examines the pricing of S&amp;P 100 calls using 14 months of transactions data. We find that market prices of S&amp;P 100 calls differ systematically from Black-Scholes values. The biases in Black-Scholes model prices are both statistically and economically significant and correspond to biases that arise if market prices incorporate a stochastically changing volatility of the index.
